# Incident Report: Unauthorized Local User Creation

## Incident Summary

A new local Windows user account was created on the monitored endpoint. User account creation is a persistence technique commonly used by attackers after initial compromise.

---

## Incident Information

| Field | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Incident Name | New Local User Detection |
| Severity | Medium |
| Event ID | 4720 |
| Detection Source | Microsoft Sentinel |
| Data Source | Windows Security Logs |
| Affected Machine | SOC-WIN10-01 |
| Status | Investigated |

---

## Detection Logic

The analytics rule monitors Windows Security Event ID **4720**, which is generated whenever a new local user account is created.

---

